<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172955>
    bibo:endPage "68" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "59" ;
    bibo:volume "1247" ;
    dc:creator "Kraus, Fred; Allison, Allen" ;
    dc:date "2006" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Cyrtodactylus (Lacertilia: Gekkonidae) from Papua New Guinea" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172956>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172957>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172958> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172956>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Photograph of (A) holotype of Cyrtodactylus murua, BPBM 17858, from Woodlark Island, and (B) C. louisiadensis from Sudest Island, in life. Photos by A. Allison and G. Shea, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172956/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172957>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Map of the offshore islands of Milne Bay Province, Papua New Guinea, showing localities of holotype (closed circle) and paratype (open circle) of Cyrtodactylus murua on Woodlark Island." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172957/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172958>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Photograph of the type locality. The holotype was collected ca. 4 m above the ground from the trunk of the strangling fig in the center of the photo, just to the right of the road. Note the Monstera sp. vines (left foreground) and the epiphytic Asplenium sp. ferns (center and right center) which were common in the forest. Photo by A. Allison." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172958/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

